The '''Domestic Fuels Protection Act''' ([[112th United States Congress|112th]] {{USBill |112|hr|4345}}, [[113th United States Congress|113th]] {{USBill |113|hr|1214}}) is a proposed law pending in the [[United States Congress|U.S. Congress]] to protect domestic producers and sellers of [[ethanol]], [[biodiesel]], and other clean fuels from liability to end-users who put the wrong kind of fuel or fuel mix into their tanks and suffer damage to their engines. The idea is to ensure that domestic producers of alternative fuel and related equipment aren’t put out of business due to crippling liability claims.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.congress.gov/bill/112th-congress/house-bill/4345|title=H.R.4345 - Domestic Fuels Protection Act of 2012|last=|first=|date=|website=Congress.gov|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=October 20, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/the-domestic-fuels-protection-act-2012/|title=Does the Proposed Domestic Fuels Protection Act Put a Burden on Consumers?|last=Scheer|first=Roddy|date=August 25, 2012|work=Scientific American|access-date=October 20, 2018|last2=Moss|first2=Doug}}</ref>
